    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-07-21T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-07-21T15:00:00-05:00" n="543"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d543">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.4016/2125: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-07-21T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 21, 1939—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>308. Your despatch 1043, June 23, 1939. Please address a note to Minister of
                    Foreign Affairs and referring to report published in the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Deutsche Allgemeine Zeitung</hi> concerning proposed regulations imposing
                    restrictions upon Jews visiting health and bathing resorts and add: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>I have been instructed by my Government to call attention to its several
                            representations, and particularly to those contained in the Embassy’s
                            notes of May 9<note n="59" xml:id="d543fn59">See telegram No. 63, May 7,
                                1938, 5 p.m., to the Ambassador in Germany, <ref
                                    target="frus1938v02#pg_369">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1938, vol. <hi
                                        rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 369</ref>.</note> and December
                            14, 1938<note n="59a" xml:id="d543fn59a">See telegram No. 228, December
                                10, 1938, 1 p.m., to the Chargé in Germany, <ref
                                    target="frus1938v02#pg_410">
                                    <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 410</ref>.</note> and January
                            6, 1939.<note n="60" xml:id="d543fn60">See telegram No. 2, January 6,
                                noon, to the Chargé in Germany, <ref target="#pg_576">p.
                                576</ref>.</note> against the imposition in Germany of
                            discriminations upon American citizens based on race or creed, and to
                            state that the Government of the United States assumes that the
                            discriminatory treatment indicated in the report will not be applied to
                            American nationals of the Jewish race.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
